com.camerontec.catalys.util.marketdata

Interface IMarketDataStore

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardMarketDataStore

    public interface IMarketDataStore
    Stores market data (eg prices, trading status, etc) for a market.

    • Method Detail

      • addInstrumentDepthListener

        void addInstrumentDepthListener(IInstrument instrument,
                                IInstrumentDepthListener listener,
                                String requestID)
                         throws SubscriptionException
        Register a listener to depth (aggregated) updates on the given instrument.

        If this listener is already registered, does nothing (in other words implementations must check for duplicate listeners).

        Errors

        This request to listen (ie subscribe) can fail immediately, in which case a SubscriptionException is thrown. However, it may also fail later, after the method has returned. This can happen if a corresponding subscription request needs to be sent back to a remote source of market data. In that case an request reject may come back later on. If that happens, the listeners inherited onSubscriptionError method will be called, passing in the requestID supplied on this method.
        Parameters:
        instrument - Instrument to listen to.
        listener - Object listening for updates.
        requestID - Optional identifier of this subscription request. May be null.
        Throws:
        SubscriptionException - if there was a problem making the subscription request to the underlying market data source.

      • getInstrument

        IInstrument getInstrument(String symbol)
        Return the instrument associated with the given symbol (short name).

        Market data for the instrument can be retrieved from the returned object.

        Parameters:
        symbol - Name by which the instrument is known in the market (eg ticker symbol).
        Returns:
        Instrument associated with given symbol.

      • getInstrument

        IInstrument getInstrument(BytesSegment symbolBytes)
        Similar to getInstrument(String ).

        The advantage of this method is that the symbol can be defined using the an incoming message's existing bytes, without need to create a String object.

        Parameters:
        symbolBytes - The bytes defining a symbol.
        Returns:
        Instrument associated with given symbol.

      • getInstruments

        Collection<IInstrument> getInstruments()
        Returns cloned unmodifiableCollection of all instruments known in market. It is cloned so that ConcurrentModificationException is not thrown while iterating.
        Returns:
        All known instruments.

      • getTradingStatus

        int getTradingStatus(String tradingSessionId,
                     String tradingSessionSubId)
        Returns current market trading status for a given TradingSessionID/TradingSessionSubID.

        See trading status constants.

        Parameters:
        tradingSessionId - Trading session ID
        tradingSessionSubId - Trading session ID, null if none
        Returns:
        Current trading status of the couple ID/Sub ID.

      • getTradingSessions

        Collection<String> getTradingSessions()
        Returns collection of all trading sessions known in market.
        Returns:
        All known trading sessions.

      • isAvailable

        boolean isAvailable()
        Return whether live data is currently available. Live data means that the most current data for the given exchange is available. It does not imply that the exchange is necessarily in any particular state.
        Returns:
        Whether live data is available
